relation: A colour change from the Gigaborg I did, I was amazed at how nicely the mere shifting of colours made the shadows a reddish brown, making the whole thing look more golden than I'd hoped. It was a pleasant surprise, thus why I posted it at all (well, that and "Omegaborg" just sounds cool.)
From Mother, the Gigaborg. This was the original. Also see my Omegaborg.
Note the digusting garbage water seeping out at the bottom, as well as Mr. T's sweatsock hanging over the can's rim.
From Mother. I tried to preserve the original colours on this one so I added a blue glow around the pink ghost.
A sketch that I submitted, given that I don't intend to do anything else with it.
